Preheat oven to 200 degrees. Halve, peel, and slice the @yellow onion{1}. Halve the @zucchini{1} lengthwise, then slice into ¼-inch half moons. Thinly slice the @romaine lettuce{1}. Drain and rinse the @kidney beans{1%can}. Halve, core, seed, and chop the @roma tomato{1}. Zest and juice the @lime{1}. Finely chop the @jalapeño{1}, removing the seeds if you prefer less heat.

Heat @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a large pan over medium heat. Add the onion and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook for about ~{5%minutes}, until softened, and set aside. Add the zucchini and cook, tossing, for ~{2-3%minutes}, until softened and lightly charred.

Return the onion to the pan, then add the kidney beans, @cumin{1%teaspoon}, @chipotle powder{1%teaspoon}, tomatoes, and as much jalapeño as you dare. Cook for about ~{5%minutes}, until tomatoes have softened. Taste and season with salt and pepper. Set aside.

Make the lime crema: in a small #bowl{}, thoroughly combine the @sour cream{1%tablespoon} with the lime zest. Set aside.

Wipe the pan clean with #paper towel{}. Heat one @whole wheat tortilla{1} over medium heat. Sprinkle one half of the tortilla with @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}, top with some zucchini and kidney beans, and top with more cheese. Fold over the tortilla and turn. Cook until cheese has melted, and tortilla is crispy, about ~{3%minutes}. Transfer the quesadilla to a #baking sheet{} and place in the oven to keep warm. Repeat to make the other quesadilla with the remaining @whole wheat tortilla{1} and @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}.

Make the romaine salad: toss the romaine lettuce with lime juice, @olive oil{1/2%tablespoon}, salt and pepper.

Cut the quesadillas into wedges. Serve with the lime crema and the romaine salad to the side.

> Cumin and chili powder give a one-two punch of spice and smokiness to these jam-packed veggie quesadillas. Tangy lime crema and a refreshingly crisp romaine salad help cool things off.